I once had a bunch of friends, most of whom I grew up with, I was with the girl of my dreams - my best friend and ideal girlfriend all in one: we worked together (same shift) and lived together and never got sick of each other, until after 3 years of being off heroin I relapsed, I lost everything including my mind and heart.  
I now have 19 months off heroin but I have not a single friend, and I'm not exaggerating.  I am completely and utterly alone and it is killing me. I've failed at attempting suicide multiple times (feels great when you are too much of a coward to live so you try to die and you can't even do that right, it's a whole new level of.. there is no word for it, but I'd go with  morbid despair) and now this loneliness has manifested as a constant physical pain. Maybe it is psychosomatic.. IDK, I'm getting help from a therapist but it doesn't help me find friends..Everyone just thinks everyone has an agenda, I try to make friends with a dude and they think I'm gay or something.. I try to introduce myself to a female classmate and always its either "Um I have a boyfriend" or "Ok, so what do you want?" and I'm just like... "A friend..." and I get blown off.  And the "I have a boyfriend" response, I am a STRONG advocate of monogamy and I do not do hook ups or one night stands, I'd rather form an amazing emotional connection with someone then bust a nut and feel remorse. Like I don't even know you so why would you assume I'd want to "court" you? Just cause you think you're attractive?  Well, good for you for having confidence but the whole world isn't after your "goodies"... IDK, everywhere I hear and see things like "Having no friends is like smoking a pack of cigarettes a day"  or  "Companionship = Long Happy Life" and I'm only here cause I can't hurt my Dad anymore.. my Mom passed away from drinking and I have been a shit son to my Dad in the past but he was always there for me and now he is getting a bit older and things are happening physically and he needs help and I want to take care of him and spend as much time with him as I can but if I don't find any friends or anyone when (Universe Forbid, *knock on wood*) my Dad's time comes, I don't know if I'll be able to handle it.. he's the only person in my life rn and he's my Dad, if I lost him, I have no doubt in my mind, I would shortly follow...

Our society makes it very difficult to make REAL friends, not friends who you add on Instagram/Facebook and they "Like" something everyone once and a while, JUST SO WE ARE CLEAR:  That is NOT "Keeping in touch." It's easy to blame social media but it's also people, people and their wild fears and stupid inhibitions. Then One day I walked into GameStop and the price went down a good amount and she saw me staring at it, she then proceeded to buy it for me with 2 games!
